Class AbstractAutomatonLStar<A,I,O,S,T,SP,TP,AI extends MutableDeterministic<S,I,T,SP,TP>>

  • Type Parameters:
    A - automaton class, must be a subclass of MutableDeterministic

    TP - transition property class
    All Implemented Interfaces:

    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ExtensibleAutomatonLStar

    public abstract class AbstractAutomatonLStar<A,I,O,S,T,SP,TP,AI extends MutableDeterministic<S,I,T,SP,TP>>
extends AbstractLStar<A,I,O>
    Abstract base class for algorithms that produce (subclasses of) MutableDeterministic automata. This class provides the L*-style hypothesis construction. Implementing classes solely have to specify how state and transition properties should be derived.
    Author:
    Malte Isberner

        protected abstract TP transitionProperty(Row<I> stateRow,

        Derives a transition property from the corresponding transition. N.B.: Not the transition row is passed to this method, but the row for the outgoing state. The transition row can be retrieved by stateRow.getSuccessor(inputIdx).
        Parameters:

        inputIdx - the index of the input symbol to consider
